00:55:01,181 --> 00:55:03,099
Till the dawn's early light.

719
00:55:03,266 --> 00:55:07,144
You got stamina, Lester. I wanna be you.

720
00:55:07,354 --> 00:55:10,189
Well, I'm 150 years old, so
you wouldn't be me for long.

721
00:55:20,117 --> 00:55:22,284
- Mr. Ambassador.
- Ken Taylor.

722
00:55:22,452 --> 00:55:23,953
Thank you for what you're doing.

723
00:55:24,746 --> 00:55:27,581
I was expecting more of a G-man look.

724
00:55:28,667 --> 00:55:30,668
I think you're thinking of the FBI, sir.

725
00:55:31,461 --> 00:55:33,796
Ah. This way.

726
00:55:45,934 --> 00:55:49,645
- These are blank, you know. Stamps...
- Yeah, I'll take care of this.

727
00:55:51,857 --> 00:55:52,982
How long?

728
00:55:53,191 --> 00:55:55,985
A day, prep their covers.
Two if they need it.

729
00:55:56,153 --> 00:55:57,486
And you'll fly out with them?

730
00:55:57,904 --> 00:55:59,530
Yeah.

731
00:55:59,698 --> 00:56:01,365
There's something you should know.

732
00:56:01,575 --> 00:56:04,827
We think our housekeeper
has figured out who they are.

733
00:56:05,370 --> 00:56:09,832
We don't know if we can trust
her, so sooner is better.

734
00:56:59,716 --> 00:57:01,008
Hi.

735
00:57:01,176 --> 00:57:03,052
My name's Kevin Harkins...

736
00:57:04,137 --> 00:57:05,721
...and I'm gonna get you home.

737
00:57:07,182 --> 00:57:09,808
These are the screenplays
for your cover identities.

738
00:57:11,436 --> 00:57:13,896
It's theater of the absurd.

739
00:57:14,064 --> 00:57:16,649
- What are our chances?
- Your chances are good.

740
00:57:16,816 --> 00:57:19,944
"Good"? Well, what's the
number value of "good"?

741
00:57:20,153 --> 00:57:22,863
Thirty percent chance of
being publicly executed?

742
00:57:23,031 --> 00:57:26,575
Can you tell me what the objection
was to normal cover identities?

743
00:57:26,743 --> 00:57:28,953
There are no Canadians in the
country for normal reasons.

744
00:57:29,120 --> 00:57:30,663
- They'll sniff us out regardless.
- The Swedish Consul?

745
00:57:30,830 --> 00:57:34,500
They accused him of being an American at
the airport. They held him for an hour.

746
00:57:34,668 --> 00:57:37,711
We can't hold up under that. We don't
know what the hell movie people do.

747
00:57:37,879 --> 00:57:39,004
That's why I'm here.

748
00:57:39,172 --> 00:57:42,675
I'm gonna help you. I'll be with
you the whole way. This is what I do.

749
00:57:42,842 --> 00:57:44,885
Have you gotten people
out this way before?

750
00:57:46,221 --> 00:57:47,721
This would be a first.

751
00:57:49,224 --> 00:57:52,810
Do you know that every day they catch
another friend of the shah at the airport?

752
00:57:52,978 --> 00:57:55,479
Kangaroo trials and
then firing squads...

753
00:57:55,689 --> 00:57:58,399
...just for having American
names in their phone books.

754
00:57:58,566 --> 00:58:00,025
You've been here an hour.

755
00:58:00,193 --> 00:58:02,611
And you're asking us to trust
you with our lives, Mr...?

756
00:58:02,779 --> 00:58:04,113
Harkins.

757
00:58:04,322 --> 00:58:06,115
That's your real name?

758
00:58:06,783 --> 00:58:07,950
No.

759
00:58:10,912 --> 00:58:14,707
I know there are risks
involved. Serious risks.

760
00:58:15,208 --> 00:58:16,917
But it is time to go.

761
00:58:19,379 --> 00:58:23,007
We've got orders to close the embassy and
go back. There's nowhere for them to stay.

762
00:58:25,510 --> 00:58:29,221
We will never make it through
immigration at the airport. I'm serious.

763
00:58:29,389 --> 00:58:33,309
No, no, no, this is what, the part when we
say this is so crazy it might actually work?

764
00:58:33,476 --> 00:58:35,311
Joe, I saw it in Burma.
They get people out.

765
00:58:35,478 --> 00:58:38,731
Snitches in banana republics? They get
them over the border after the coup.

766
00:58:38,898 --> 00:58:39,940
That's your opinion, Joe.

767
00:58:40,108 --> 00:58:42,276
You know, his opinion got
us out in the first place.

768
00:58:42,777 --> 00:58:46,905
If we go out there with fake passports,
we are spies, period. That's execution.

769
00:58:47,073 --> 00:58:49,616
- You got a problem lying, Joe?
- Point is, we can't stay here.

770
00:58:50,285 --> 00:58:53,912
If we get caught, you and Pat go on trial
for harboring the enemy, you know that?

771
00:58:54,080 --> 00:58:56,665
Pat and I have discussed
it. It's the risk we took.

772
00:58:57,459 --> 00:59:00,377
That man out there has got bad
cards and he is going to lose.

773
00:59:00,545 --> 00:59:03,839
And if he loses, it's our lives.

774
00:59:05,133 --> 00:59:07,134
And his life too.

775
00:59:08,553 --> 00:59:10,471
Look, we don't have any alternatives.

776
00:59:10,638 --> 00:59:11,847
We gotta go.

777
00:59:18,355 --> 00:59:21,815
These cover identities were created
specifically for each one of you.

778
00:59:21,983 --> 00:59:24,526
What you need to do is memorize
everything that's inside.

779
00:59:24,694 --> 00:59:27,613
Who you are, what you are,
where you've been. Complete bio.

780
00:59:27,781 --> 00:59:28,864
And then add to that.

781
00:59:29,032 --> 00:59:32,451
Where do you vacation? What are your
allergies? Who'd you have an affair with?

782
00:59:32,619 --> 00:59:33,786
The only way this works...

783
00:59:33,953 --> 00:59:37,623
...is if you believe that you're these
people so much that you dream like them.

784
00:59:38,583 --> 00:59:40,292
Get started tonight.

785
00:59:41,002 --> 00:59:44,004
I'll be back tomorrow.
We'll get going. Good luck.

786
00:59:49,594 --> 00:59:51,303
Well, my guy kind of sucks.

787
00:59:51,471 --> 00:59:52,846
What's your name?

788
00:59:53,556 --> 00:59:55,849
Mike McEwan, eh? Heh.

789
00:59:56,810 --> 00:59:57,851
That was convincing.

790
00:59:58,019 --> 00:59:59,686
Kathy, what's your name?

791
01:00:27,674 --> 01:00:30,884
The Love Boat will be
seen 15 minutes from now.

792
01:00:31,052 --> 01:00:34,847
The State Department insisted today
that the crisis in Afghanistan...

793
01:00:35,014 --> 01:00:39,101
...will not divert the attention of the
United States from the plight of the hostages.

794
01:00:39,269 --> 01:00:41,979
...is perceived to be if not
impotent, then at least reluctant...

795
01:00:42,147 --> 01:00:46,650
Now the United States finds itself in such
bitter confrontation with the Soviet Union...

796
01:00:46,818 --> 01:00:49,653
...over that country's
invasion of Afghanistan...

797
01:00:49,863 --> 01:00:52,281
The United States is now
moving toward a decision...

798
01:00:52,449 --> 01:00:54,491
...to boycott the Summer
Olympics in Moscow...

799
01:00:55,660 --> 01:00:58,871
Bad news, bad news. Even when
it's good news, it's bad news.

800
01:00:59,247 --> 01:01:03,375
John Wayne's in the ground six
months, this is what's left of America.

801
01:01:31,905 --> 01:01:35,532
"The Minister of Culture and Guidance
has approved your location scout.

802
01:01:35,700 --> 01:01:37,618
He will send his representative
to meet you and your crew...

803
01:01:37,785 --> 01:01:41,371
...at the Khayyam entrance to the
Grand Bazaar tomorrow at 3 p. m. "

804
01:01:42,248 --> 01:01:43,415
They called your bluff.

805
01:01:43,583 --> 01:01:46,168
- Maybe they're cooperating.
- Absolutely not.

806
01:01:46,586 --> 01:01:50,964
Seven Americans walking the bazaar
is asking for a riot. It's the hive.

807
01:01:51,132 --> 01:01:52,466
Seven Canadians, Jack.

808
01:01:52,634 --> 01:01:55,761
Never give them multiple
shots at a cover.

809
01:01:56,471 --> 01:01:57,763
Are they even ready?

810
01:01:57,931 --> 01:01:59,181
They're getting there.

811
01:01:59,349 --> 01:02:00,891
There's no prize for "Most Improved. "

812
01:02:01,059 --> 01:02:03,769
I don't have a choice. We say no,
they show up at the residence...

813
01:02:03,937 --> 01:02:06,563
...and drag everyone out. You think
their covers are gonna hold up...

814
01:02:06,731 --> 01:02:08,565
...when they're getting
their fingernails pulled out?

815
01:02:29,337 --> 01:02:32,589
You want us to go to the Grand
Bazaar at 3:00 in the afternoon?

816
01:02:33,675 --> 01:02:36,677
You said a day to learn our covers,
then straight to the airport.

817
01:02:36,844 --> 01:02:38,470
They suspect something?

818
01:02:38,638 --> 01:02:41,390
What I know is, we need to
pretend to be a movie crew.

819
01:02:41,558 --> 01:02:44,977
We go to the bazaar today, we
fly out from the airport tomorrow.

820
01:02:47,063 --> 01:02:48,480
We won't do it.

821
01:02:50,275 --> 01:02:52,985
He told them that there were six
of us. So they're expecting six.

822
01:02:53,152 --> 01:02:55,362
It would be suspicious not
to show up at this point.

823
01:02:55,530 --> 01:02:57,656
What else do we have to do, all right?

824
01:02:57,824 --> 01:03:00,367
He's about to show them the
only cards that we're holding...

825
01:03:00,535 --> 01:03:04,204
- which is that they don't know we're here!
- That's the ball game, okay?

826
01:03:04,372 --> 01:03:06,498
Look, we don't have any other choice!

827
01:03:06,666 --> 01:03:09,001
Who says that we'll know
our covers well enough?

828
01:03:09,168 --> 01:03:10,919
We're not in the CIA.

829
01:03:12,046 --> 01:03:13,672
It's suicide.

830
01:03:13,840 --> 01:03:15,924
I'm asking you to trust me.

831
01:03:17,343 --> 01:03:18,510
I don't trust you.

832
01:03:21,055 --> 01:03:23,599
This is the game, Joe. What
world are you living in?

833
01:03:23,766 --> 01:03:27,394
The one where they're hanging
people from construction cranes, Bob.

834
01:03:28,187 --> 01:03:30,647
It's too dangerous. I won't
bring my wife into the bazaar.

835
01:03:32,734 --> 01:03:34,067
Joe?

836
01:03:40,783 --> 01:03:42,618
So we'll see you at 2.

837
01:04:05,475 --> 01:04:10,562
So don't be recognizable but look
exactly like your passport photo.

838
01:04:11,814 --> 01:04:14,274
I haven't been this
nervous since our wedding.

839
01:04:16,069 --> 01:04:18,153
Only this isn't a huge
mistake, hopefully.

840
01:04:19,614 --> 01:04:21,490
Sorry. Okay.

841
01:04:24,243 --> 01:04:30,083
Hello?

842
01:04:38,466 --> 01:04:39,758
Who was that?

843
01:04:43,096 --> 01:04:44,805
- Mark?
- Yeah?

844
01:04:47,100 --> 01:04:48,684
I'm scared.

845
01:04:51,020 --> 01:04:52,270
It's okay.

846
01:05:40,153 --> 01:05:41,319
Where are they?

847
01:05:41,487 --> 01:05:42,821
In the kitchen.

848
01:05:59,756 --> 01:06:03,216
This is what I do. I get people out.

849
01:06:04,719 --> 01:06:07,554
And I've never left anyone behind.

850
01:06:09,265 --> 01:06:11,600
I wish I could believe you, Mr. Harkins.

851
01:06:16,731 --> 01:06:20,025
My name is Tony Mendez.
I'm from New York.

852
01:06:20,193 --> 01:06:22,944
My father worked construction. My
mother teaches elementary school.

853
01:06:23,112 --> 01:06:25,489
I have a wife and
a 10-year-old son.

854
01:06:27,909 --> 01:06:32,579
You play along with me today, I promise
you, I will get you out tomorrow.

855
01:06:36,959 --> 01:06:38,668
Fuck.

856
01:07:19,252 --> 01:07:21,127
Shit.

857
01:07:48,155 --> 01:07:49,656
Hang on.

858
01:08:37,830 --> 01:08:39,456
You all right?

859
01:08:44,712 --> 01:08:46,880
Okay. Tell me who you are.

860
01:08:47,590 --> 01:08:49,841
Mike McEwan, cameraman.

861
01:08:50,384 --> 01:08:52,594
Robert Baker, director.

862
01:08:53,054 --> 01:08:55,055
Timothy Harris, location manager.

863
01:08:55,222 --> 01:08:57,223
Mary Ann Boyd, screenwriter.

864
01:08:57,391 --> 01:08:59,142
Rachel Dewart, production designer.

865
01:08:59,352 --> 01:09:01,061
Sean Bissett, associate producer.

866
01:09:01,228 --> 01:09:03,772
All right. Let's go make a movie.

867
01:09:17,078 --> 01:09:19,079
Welcome, welcome. My
name is Reza Bolhani.

868
01:09:19,246 --> 01:09:21,623
- Kevin Harkins. I'm the producer.
- Nice to meet you.

869
01:09:21,791 --> 01:09:23,416
This is Mike McEwan, our cameraman.

870
01:09:23,584 --> 01:09:25,794
This is Tim. This is
Mary, our screenwriter.

871
01:09:25,962 --> 01:09:27,462
And this is our director, Bob Baker.

872
01:09:27,630 --> 01:09:29,381
- You are the director?
- Yes.

873
01:09:29,548 --> 01:09:32,008
Is this film a foreign-bride film?

874
01:09:32,927 --> 01:09:34,219
Sorry?

875
01:09:34,387 --> 01:09:36,846
A film where a foreign
bride comes to Iran...

876
01:09:37,014 --> 01:09:40,558
...but she doesn't understand
the language or the customs...

877
01:09:40,726 --> 01:09:43,269
...and there is
misunderstandings and laughs.

878
01:09:43,437 --> 01:09:44,896
Oh, no.

879
01:09:50,111 --> 01:09:55,573
The bazaar in Tehran is one
of the largest in the world.

880
01:09:56,158 --> 01:10:00,328
This bazaar has been on this
spot for over 8000 years.

881
01:10:00,496 --> 01:10:04,708
You can find many items
such as paper, spices...

882
01:10:04,917 --> 01:10:07,419
...precious metals, all right here.

883
01:10:07,586 --> 01:10:08,795
Right this way, please.

884
01:10:14,176 --> 01:10:15,552
This way.

885
01:10:30,651 --> 01:10:31,943
- Uh, Mike?
- Yeah.

886
01:10:32,111 --> 01:10:35,131
If I was to say you're looking through
the wrong end of that viewfinder,

887
01:10:35,132 --> 01:10:36,281
...would I be right?

888
01:10:38,576 --> 01:10:40,160
Yup.

889
01:10:47,376 --> 01:10:48,501
Just a little further.

890
01:11:18,491 --> 01:11:21,743
Please wait here. Let's stay together.

891
01:11:38,552 --> 01:11:40,303
He wants the photograph you took.

892
01:11:40,471 --> 01:11:43,556
It's okay, it's her job to take
photographs. She's the production designer.

893
01:11:43,724 --> 01:11:46,976
He says he did not give you permission
to take a photograph of his store.

894
01:11:47,144 --> 01:11:49,813
That's okay. You can
tell him he can have it.

895
01:11:51,107 --> 01:11:53,191
Please, please, just
take the photograph.

896
01:12:02,993 --> 01:12:04,035
Peace be upon you.

897
01:12:04,203 --> 01:12:05,578
SAHAR: And upon you, sir. Welcome.

898
01:12:05,746 --> 01:12:06,996
I hope you are well.

899
01:12:07,164 --> 01:12:08,832
Thank you very much. How are you?

900
01:12:09,041 --> 01:12:11,417
I'm very well. What's your name?

901
01:12:11,585 --> 01:12:12,752
Sahar.

902
01:12:23,764 --> 01:12:26,933
He's saying that the shah killed
his son with an American gun.

903
01:12:36,610 --> 01:12:38,987
No, no, no! No! Canada!

904
01:12:39,155 --> 01:12:40,196
Canada!

905
01:12:40,364 --> 01:12:42,657
I would like to suggest
that we end our visit.

906
01:12:52,001 --> 01:12:53,084
You know, sister...

907
01:12:53,252 --> 01:12:57,255
...those who are with him, Rasool of
Allah, we are tender among ourselves.

908
01:12:57,423 --> 01:12:58,965
But stern against the Kufar.

909
01:12:59,592 --> 01:13:01,009
As God wills it.

910
01:13:02,636 --> 01:13:05,847
But those who sit silently have sinned.

911
01:13:07,308 --> 01:13:09,309
How else may I help, sir?

912
01:13:09,476 --> 01:13:11,811
No, no, just one thing.

913
01:13:13,689 --> 01:13:15,315
How long have they been here?

914
01:13:16,567 --> 01:13:17,609
Pardon?

915
01:13:18,944 --> 01:13:20,653
The guests of the Ambassador.

916
01:13:20,654 --> 01:13:22,030
The guests of the Ambassador.
How long have they been here?

917
01:13:24,909 --> 01:13:26,492
They arrived two days ago.

918
01:13:27,286 --> 01:13:31,998
Forgive my intrusion,
one must be vigilant.

919
01:13:33,292 --> 01:13:36,169
Everyone in this house
is a friend of Iran.

920
01:14:10,704 --> 01:14:12,163
How'd it go?

921
01:14:13,791 --> 01:14:15,416
What about tomorrow?

922
01:14:16,752 --> 01:14:18,294
Tomorrow they'll be ready.

923
01:14:22,216 --> 01:14:24,509
For Kennedy, a stunning turnaround...

924
01:14:24,677 --> 01:14:26,719
...one week after
humiliation in Illinois.

925
01:14:26,887 --> 01:14:28,179
I love New York.

926
01:14:29,556 --> 01:14:32,100
And I love Connecticut too.

927
01:14:32,268 --> 01:14:34,894
How did he win here? Well, he had help.

928
01:14:35,062 --> 01:14:39,691
I'm responsible for anything that
goes wrong in this government.

929
01:14:39,858 --> 01:14:43,903
A man in Scranton is placing a flag
in his lawn for every day of captivity.

930
01:14:44,905 --> 01:14:48,032
When he runs out of lawn,
Kennedy wins the primary.

931
01:14:48,575 --> 01:14:50,994
The six with the
Canadians are coming out.

932
01:15:02,047 --> 01:15:03,631
Who signed off on this?

933
01:15:03,799 --> 01:15:06,592
- You. Where was your passport issued?
- Vancouver.

934
01:15:06,760 --> 01:15:08,052
- Where were you born?
- Toronto.

935
01:15:08,220 --> 01:15:10,221
"Torono. " Canadians
don't pronounce the T.

936
01:15:10,389 --> 01:15:12,807
Some Komiteh guard is
actually gonna know that?

937
01:15:12,975 --> 01:15:16,769
If you're detained for questioning, they
will bring in someone who knows that. Yes.

938
01:15:16,937 --> 01:15:20,148
Mary, who were the last three
prime ministers of Canada?

939
01:15:20,607 --> 01:15:23,109
Trudeau, Pearson and Diefenbaker.

940
01:15:23,277 --> 01:15:24,944
- What's your father's name?
- Howard.

941
01:15:25,112 --> 01:15:26,863
- What's his occupation?
- Fisherman.

942
01:15:27,031 --> 01:15:29,282
- Where were you born?
- Halifax, Nova Scotia.

943
01:15:29,450 --> 01:15:31,200
What's your date of birth?

944
01:15:31,368 --> 01:15:33,536
February 21st, 1952.

945
01:15:33,746 --> 01:15:35,663
- Good. What's your job on the movie?
- Producer.

946
01:15:35,831 --> 01:15:38,583
- Associate. Last movie you produced?
- High and Dry.

947
01:15:38,751 --> 01:15:40,251
- Who paid for that?
- CFDC.

948
01:15:40,419 --> 01:15:42,754
What's your middle name?
What's your middle name?

949
01:15:42,921 --> 01:15:44,630
- Leon?
- Shoot him. He's an American spy.

950
01:15:46,342 --> 01:15:50,094
Look, they're gonna try to break you,
okay? By trying to get you agitated.

951
01:15:50,262 --> 01:15:52,388
You have to know your
resume back to front.

952
01:15:52,556 --> 01:15:55,601
You really believe your little story's
gonna make a difference...

953
01:15:55,602 --> 01:15:56,893
...when there's a gun to our heads?

954
01:15:57,811 --> 01:16:00,980
I think my story's the only thing
between you and a gun to your head.

955
01:16:04,318 --> 01:16:05,360
Okay.

956
01:16:10,574 --> 01:16:13,534
Hey, they made it through
the location scout.

