01:48:27,592 --> 01:48:29,719
- I thought we did.
- Ha.

1202
01:48:30,387 --> 01:48:33,180
Carter said you were a great American.

1203
01:48:33,890 --> 01:48:35,558
Great American what?

1204
01:48:36,101 --> 01:48:37,560
He didn't say.

1205
01:48:50,907 --> 01:48:52,158
What happened to your picture?

1206
01:48:53,785 --> 01:48:54,994
It's in turnaround.

1207
01:49:37,287 --> 01:49:38,871
Can I come in?

1208
01:50:24,877 --> 01:50:28,788
The Iran Hostage Crisis ended
on January 20, 1981,

1209
01:50:28,789 --> 01:50:33,221
...when all remaining hostages were released.
They spent 444 days in captivity.

1210
01:50:37,222 --> 01:50:40,299
The involvement of the
C.I.A. complemented efforts of

1211
01:50:40,300 --> 01:50:43,490
the Canadian embassy in
freeing the six held in Tehran.

1212
01:50:43,530 --> 01:50:46,166
To this day, this story
stands as an enduring model

1213
01:50:46,167 --> 01:50:48,650
for international cooperation
between governments.

1214
01:50:48,776 --> 01:50:53,261
All of the Houseguests
returned to the U.S. Foreign Service

1215
01:50:53,262 --> 01:50:55,204
after their ordeal in Iran.

1216
01:50:56,742 --> 01:51:01,872
Oscar-winning makeup artist John Chambers
was awarded the C.I.A.'s Intelligence Medal,

1217
01:51:01,898 --> 01:51:03,385
its highest civilian honor.

1218
01:51:03,386 --> 01:51:06,745
He and Mendez remained friends until
Chambers' death in 2001.

1219
01:51:08,504 --> 01:51:11,935
Tony Mendez's Intelligence Star
was returned to him in 1997,

1220
01:51:11,961 --> 01:51:15,504
when the Argo operation was
declassified by President Clinton.

1221
01:51:25,521 --> 01:51:31,497
He lives in rural Maryland with his family.

1222
01:53:25,932 --> 01:53:31,136
They went in, as you know, under the
guise of creating a motion-picture film.

1223
01:53:31,146 --> 01:53:35,874
But that it had a very
high possibility of failure.

1224
01:53:35,942 --> 01:53:38,235
And after it was successful, of course...

1225
01:53:38,403 --> 01:53:41,196
...it was a great temptation
to reveal all the stories...

1226
01:53:41,364 --> 01:53:44,883
...so maybe I could take a little bit of
credit for it, since I was president...

1227
01:53:44,951 --> 01:53:50,138
...but we had to keep it secret.
Tony Mendez has gone down in CIA history...

1228
01:53:50,206 --> 01:53:51,582
...after his retirement...

1229
01:53:51,750 --> 01:53:57,689
...as one of the 50 most important
CIA operatives of all time.

1230
01:53:59,215 --> 01:54:04,595
Eventually we got every hostage
back home, safe and sound...

1231
01:54:04,763 --> 01:54:08,766
...and we upheld the integrity of
our country, and we did it peacefully.

